Essa palestra aborda desenvolvimentos recentes e se aprofunda em técnicas de utilização do Android Market que visam alavancar novos modelos de monetização, entregar conteúdo otimizado, minimizar a pirataria e maximizar a visibilidade do seu aplicativo., sessionurl: http://www.google.com/intl/pt-BR/events/developerday/2011/sao-paulo/agenda/session_2000.html

entry.title: Row: 5
entry.content: sessiondate: Sunday, November 13, sessiontime: 11:40-12:30, sessionroom: [Android], sessionproduct: Android, sessiontrack: Android, sessiontitle: High-performance graphics for Android, sessiontags: 2003, sessionabstract: The Android framework offers developers a wide choice of options for delivering rich, immersive, interactive graphics to users. This talk surveys the options, including the 2D and 3D graphics capabilities available through Dalvik, Renderscript, and the use of NDK.

entry.title: Row: 6
entry.content: sessiondate: Sunday, November 13, sessiontime: 13:30-14:20, sessionroom: [Android], sessionproduct: Android, sessiontrack: Android, sessiontitle: Excellence in the Android User Experience, sessiontags: 2001, sessionabstract: This talk focuses on how to produce Android applications that make users happy. It surveys a range of techniques for increasing performance, usability, and visual appeal. In particular, it covers designing applications to please users in the tablet environment.

entry.title: Row: 7
entry.content: sessiondate: Sunday, November 13, sessiontime: 14:20-15:10, sessionroom: [Android], sessionproduct: Android, sessiontrack: Android, sessiontitle: Android Market for Developers, sessiontags: 2000, sessionabstract: Android Market is undergoing continuous revisions to improve the experience for developers and end-users. This talk covers recent developments, and goes into depth on techniques for using Android Market to leverage new monetization models, deliver optimized content, minimize piracy, and maximize application visibility.

entry.title: Row: 8
entry.content: sessiondate: Sunday, November 13, sessiontime: 15:10-16:00, sessionroom: [Android], sessionproduct: Android, sessiontrack: Android, sessiontitle: Google TV: Open for Android Developers, sessiontags: 2002, sessionabstract: With the Honeycomb version of Google TV, Android developers can now create applications for the largest screen in the house! Often, the difference between a good and a great Google TV application relies as much on UI design as it does on the proper use of Android APIs. In this session we will show examples and best practices how to improve application usability and performance resulting in outstanding applications for Google TV and other Android platforms.

entry.title: Row: 9
entry.content: sessiondate: Sunday, November 13, sessiontime: 16:00-16:50, sessionroom: [Android], sessionproduct: Android, sessiontrack: Android, sessiontitle: Android Market for Developers, sessiontags: 8003, sessionabstract: Take your app to the next level with tools that help you build a real business on mobile. Learn how AdMob and Google can help you earn money from your app, drive app installs and track performance. Walk away with best practices from top app developers, including cross-promotion with house ads and why mediation is key to maximizing in-app advertising revenues.

entry.title: Row: 10
entry.content: sessiondate: Sunday, November 13, sessiontime: 10:50-11:40, sessionroom: <WEB>, sessionproduct: Chrome, HTML5, sessiontrack: Chrome & HTML5, sessiontitle: Bleeding Edge HTML5, sessiontags: 1002, sessionabstract: You may have heard of HTML5, but what's new? This session will cover some of the bleeding edge features in Chrome and the open web platform. Digging into performance, real-time communication, and system integration, we'll cover WebSockets, messaging, and rich media APIs like the Web Audio API.

entry.title: Row: 11
entry.content: sessiondate: Sunday, November 13, sessiontime: 11:40-12:30, sessionroom: <WEB>, sessionproduct: Chrome, HTML5, sessiontrack: Chrome & HTML5, sessiontitle: Making Your Web Apps Accessible Using HTML5 and ChromeVox, sessiontags: 1000, sessionabstract: When you build web apps that are interactive and dynamic, how do you make them accessible to users with disabilities? How can ChromeVox, a screen reader for Chrome, help you to test apps for accessibility? With proven HTML5 techniques, web developers can provide an experience that's just as rich and interactive for people who use assistive technology. The emphasis of this talk will be on methods that work today, with the latest browser versions. We'll cover proper use of ARIA along with focus management, keyboard navigation, and simple UI testing for accessibility with ChromeVox.

entry.title: Row: 12
entry.content: sessiondate: Sunday, November 13, sessiontime: 13:30-14:20, sessionroom: <WEB>, sessionproduct: Chrome, HTML5, sessiontrack: Chrome & HTML5, sessiontitle: Working Off the Grid: HTML5 Offline, sessiontags: 1001, sessionabstract: Giving users a flawless offline experience is tough. This session will discuss advanced offline capabilities like IndexedDB, FileSystem, AppCache, WebSQL, and online events for building great apps that work seamlessly offline.

entry.title: Row: 13
entry.content: sessiondate: Sunday, November 13, sessiontime: 14:20-15:10, sessionroom: <WEB>, sessionproduct: Chrome, HTML5, sessiontrack: Chrome & HTML5, sessiontitle: OAuth and OpenID for Data Access and Identity in web apps, sessiontags: 8000, sessionabstract: Learn how web applications can use OAuth 2.0 to access user data stored in Google's cloud for enhancing app functionality. We'll also cover using OAuth 2.0 and OpenID Connect to enable seamless site authentication without the need for additional passwords. Ease of implementation and UX are important topics and will be discussed in the context of the Google Identity Toolkit and Account Chooser.
